originalText.text: I enter the garage and  stop at the sign that says “stop here and see attendant.” The attendant tells me to park the car inside of the garage into one of the available spaces. What is the point of the sign that says stop here see attendant if they’re giving directions to park the car? Furthermore what’s the sense of valet parking if they want you to park the car ?  When I refused to park my car for the valet persons I was told that the lot was full. The service here is extremely poor. Avoid at all costs.
